{
  "stem": "3952.5",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then my brother went into this farmer whose shack it was, and he gave him two or three cigarettes that he had.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the farmer let us in into the-- how do you call the place where the cows are?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Like the barn?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The barn, where the cows are, in a barn?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He allowed us to go into the barn with the cows, and we laid on the cows to warm up.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that saved our lives, because we had to wait till, like, 10:00 in the evening.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If we had to stay out there till 10 o'clock, I don't believe we would have survived it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then-- so we warmed up, and he gave us some hot water to drink instead of tea.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Hot water, just water.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He didn't have tea.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And at 10:00 came the trucks and took us towards-- towards Milano, towards Milano, into Italy.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And as we are driving, sure enough one of the trucks, the driver fell asleep, goes into a ditch, truck turns around.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they take out all the women.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They say, go into another truck.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the men, go hide into the field until the morning when they will come-- another truck will come and pick us up.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We went-- I can tell you, this was wintertime.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The sun was shining beautifully.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The fields were frozen on the top only.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And when you stepped in, you walked into water and mud till, like, almost your knees.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And it was cold, of course, and you had to hide in the forest so that the Italians-- the Italian [INAUDIBLE]-- don't catch us and don't put us over the border again, so we don't have to redo it next week again, the same crossing the border.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we hid there until another truck came.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
